@using RentoomBookingWeb.Components.Features.Home.Components
<main class="torun-location-page">
    <section class="hero-section">
        <div class="content-shell">
            <div class="hero-badge">Torun • location • access • map</div>
            <h1>Where Torun is located and why it works well as a city stay base</h1>
            <p class="hero-lead">
                Torun is located in northern Poland on the Vistula River, in the Kuyavian-Pomeranian Voivodeship.
                It is a practical destination for a weekend break, a family stay, or an overnight stop when you want
                easy access to the Old Town and the main approach routes.
            </p>

            <div class="hero-actions">
                <a class="action-button action-button-primary" href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Toru%C5%84" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open Torun in Google Maps</a>
                <a class="action-button action-button-secondary" href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Rynek+Staromiejski+Toru%C5%84" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Old Town Square</a>
                <a class="action-button action-button-secondary" href="https://torun.pl/pl/turystyka/jak-dojechac" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Access information</a>
            </div>

            <div class="summary-grid">
                <article class="summary-card">
                    <h2>On the Vistula</h2>
                    <p>Torun sits on the Vistula River, which shapes the cityscape and creates easy access to riverside walks and viewpoints.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="summary-card">
                    <h2>Kuyavian-Pomeranian Region</h2>
                    <p>The city is one of the key urban centers of the region and an established destination for business and leisure travel.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="summary-card">
                    <h2>UNESCO Old Town</h2>
                    <p>The medieval center of Torun is one of the most valuable historic urban complexes in Poland and draws visitors year-round.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="summary-card">
                    <h2>Easy Access</h2>
                    <p>You can comfortably reach Torun by car or train, and the nearest passenger airport is in Bydgoszcz.</p>
                </article>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
        <div class="content-shell two-column-layout">
            <div class="content-panel prose-panel">
                <div class="section-header">
                    <h2>Where exactly is Torun?</h2>
                    <p>
                        Torun is located in the eastern part of the Torun Basin. This setting is convenient for both tourists
                        and business travelers. The combination of the Vistula River, a compact historic core, and direct access
                        routes makes the city suitable for both short and longer stays.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <p>
                    The best-known area is the Old Town with the Old Town Market Square, Town Hall, and a dense mix of landmarks,
                    restaurants, and cafes. For most visitors this is the natural starting point for exploring the city.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Torun works well for a city break, a family stay, or a romantic weekend. A visit can easily combine
                    sightseeing, riverside walks, museums, and the dining offer concentrated around the center.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Approximate coordinates for Torun Old Town are <strong>53.0130 N, 18.5986 E</strong>, which can help while planning navigation.
                </p>
            </div>

            <aside class="content-panel info-panel">
                <h2>Key facts</h2>
                <ul class="fact-list">
                    <li><strong>Region:</strong> Kuyavian-Pomeranian Voivodeship</li>
                    <li><strong>River:</strong> Vistula</li>
                    <li><strong>City center:</strong> Old Town Market Square</li>
                    <li><strong>Nearest airport:</strong> Bydgoszcz, about 50 km</li>
                    <li><strong>Access:</strong> by car, train, and regional airports</li>
                </ul>
            </aside>
        </div>
    </section>
 <ApartmentsSection />
    <section class="content-section map-section">
        <div class="content-shell">
            <div class="section-header section-header-wide">
                <h2>Torun map</h2>
                <p>The embedded OpenStreetMap view lets visitors understand the city layout and the location of the Old Town without leaving the page.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="map-frame-card">
                <iframe
                    title="Torun map in OpenStreetMap"
                    src="https://www.openstreetmap.org/export/embed.html?bbox=18.5190%2C52.9700%2C18.7000%2C53.0700&amp;layer=mapnik&amp;marker=53.0130%2C18.5986"
                    loading="lazy"
                    referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade"
                    class="map-frame">
                </iframe>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
        <div class="content-shell">
            <div class="section-header section-header-wide">
                <h2>Useful maps and links</h2>
                <p>These links make it easier to plan a route, find the city center, and check official visitor information.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="links-grid">
                <a class="link-card" href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Toru%C5%84" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                    <strong>Torun in Google Maps</strong>
                    <span>Fast city overview and route planning</span>
                </a>
                <a class="link-card" href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Rynek+Staromiejski+Toru%C5%84" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                    <strong>Old Town Market Square</strong>
                    <span>A practical starting point for sightseeing</span>
                </a>
                <a class="link-card" href="https://www.openstreetmap.org/search?query=Toru%C5%84" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                    <strong>Torun in OpenStreetMap</strong>
                    <span>An alternative city map view</span>
                </a>
                <a class="link-card" href="https://visittorun.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                    <strong>Official Torun tourism portal</strong>
                    <span>Attractions, inspiration, and visitor planning</span>
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section faq-section">
        <div class="content-shell">
            <div class="section-header section-header-wide">
                <h2>Quick FAQ</h2>
                <p>Short answers to common questions about the location of Torun.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-list">
                <details>
                    <summary>Which region is Torun in?</summary>
                    <p>Torun is in the Kuyavian-Pomeranian Voivodeship.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>Which river does Torun lie on?</summary>
                    <p>The city is located on the Vistula River.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>Is Torun easy to reach by train?</summary>
                    <p>Yes. Torun has convenient rail connections with major Polish cities, which makes it a good option for a short city break.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>Where should visitors start sightseeing?</summary>
                    <p>The best place to begin is the Old Town Market Square and the immediate area around the historic center.</p>
                </details>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</main>
